
[1]lover

   LOV'ER, n.

   1. One who loves; one who has a tender affection, particularly for a
   female.

   Love is blind, and lovers cannot see -

   2. A friend; one who regards with kindness.

   Your brother and his lover have embraced.

   3. One who likes or is pleased with any thing; as a lover of books or
   of science; a lover of wine; a lover of religion.

   Lover and loover. [See Louver.]
